程序包 org.janusgraph.core.log

接口 TransactionId

所有已知实现类:
StandardTransactionId
public interface TransactionId
Identifies a transaction. Used when processing user log entries to know which transaction caused a given change. A transaction is uniquely identified by the unique identifier of the instance that executed the transaction, the time of the transaction, and an instance local transaction id.

Note, that all 3 pieces of information are required for a unique identification of the transaction.

作者:
Matthias Broecheler (me@matthiasb.com)

  • 方法概要

    修饰符和类型 方法 说明
    String getInstanceId()
    Returns the unique id of the JanusGraph graph instance which executed the transaction.
    long getTransactionId()
    Returns the unique transaction id within a particular JanusGraph instance.
    Instant getTransactionTime()
    Returns the time of the transaction
